{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Wht1pzLrsdmQT7LYUdA8YF","type":"tool_result","content":"A Spark data processing environment has been deployed, but several runtime issues are preventing\nthe system from functioning correctly. Your task is to diagnose and fix these issues using\nkubectl commands - you should NOT modify any YAML files directly.\n\nCurrent symptoms:\n- The spark-data-processor Job is suspended and not running\n- The monitoring deployment pods are in ImagePullBackOff state\n- A batch job is suspended and not running\n- Configuration appears to have incorrect values\n\nYour task is to fix all issues using kubectl commands such as:\n- kubectl patch\n- kubectl edit\n- kubectl scale\n- kubectl rollout\n- kubectl exec\n- kubectl logs\n\nDo NOT modify the YAML files in cases/spark/spark_runtime_ops/resource/\n\nIMPORTANT: Do NOT scale down the Spark cluster (spark-master and spark-worker deployments).\nThe cluster must remain running throughout the task. If you encounter resource constraints,\nconsider temporarily scaling down non-essential components like spark-monitor instead.\n\nSuccess criteria:\n1. Job 'spark-data-processor' completes successfully (not suspended)\n2. Deployment 'spark-monitor' has all pods Running\n3. Job 'spark-batch-processor' completes successfully\n4. ConfigMap 'spark-config' has spark.executor.memory set to at least \"512m\"\n5. Secret 'spark-credentials' has a valid api-key (not containing \"EXPIRED\")\n6. Spark cluster (spark-master and spark-worker deployments) must remain running with at least 1 replica each===PRECOND===\n[precondition:spark_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'spark_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n spark-runtime get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n3","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eacedd33-31e1-4ecd-be67-03f0740ec2f3","uuid":"206a8822-0323-4464-b525-d3d8a2ee5003","timestamp":"2026-06-18T09:34:20.021Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"A Spark data p